This paper is about a software platform for evolutionary multi-objective optimization, which involves using algorithms to optimize multiple objectives simultaneously. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.SY (systems and control), and cs.CE (computational engineering). Among these, cs.NE is the most likely category, as it specifically deals with evolutionary algorithms. However, the other categories are also relevant, as they involve optimization, learning, and control, which are all important aspects of multi-objective optimization.
